article.headline: Liberty 19, Lafayette 13
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- Mike Brown rushed for one touchdown and passed for another as Liberty held off Lafayette 19-13 on Saturday night. Brown rushed for 88 yards on 20 carries, including a 1-yard score in the first quarter, and was 29-for-36 for 256 yards. He threw a 29-yard touchdown pass to Chris Summers with 2:01 left in the first half, but the extra point attempt was blocked. Matt Bevins' 26-yard field goal gave the Flames (2-1) a 16-0 lead as time expired in the first half. The Leopards (1-1) finally scored on Maurice White's 4-yard touchdown run, then Bevins kicked a 37-yarder to give Liberty a 19-7 lead with 4:20 left. Lafayette's Rob Curley threw a 31-yard touchdown pass to Mark Layton with 3:07 remaining to pull within 19-13, but Davis Rodriguez's extra point attempt was blocked. The Flames used an eight-play, 27-yard drive to run out the clock.
